A Siaya 2017 elections Woman Rep contender Florence Aluodo has died after a long illness.  Aluodo died while receiving treatment at a hospital in Nairobi.  She competed against Woman Representative Christine Ombaka and lost to her.  Aluodo vied as an Independent candidate after decamping from Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) over claims of shambolic nominations.  She campaigned alongside ODM leader Raila Odinga first cousin, former Gem MP Jakoyo Midiwo and former Rarieda MP Nicholas Gumbo.  She also worked with various Non-Governmental Organisations for more than 10 years.  Veteran politician and ODM leader Raila Odinga’s cousin Jakoyo Midiwo also died today.  The 54-year-old ex-MP died at Nairobi Hospital.  Jakoyo’s cousin Ruth Odinga while confirming the tragic news said the former legislator suffered a cardiac arrest.    DP Ruto challenges Raila Odinga and Kalonzo Musyoka to unite and face him in the 2022 elections  Raila and Kalonzo's unity plot ahead of 2022 general elections | INSIDE POLITICS WITH BEN KITILI  THE GRAND REPORT: Trip down memory lane on the relationship between President Uhuru and Raila Odinga By James Omoro | 4 hours ago By Olivia Odhiambo | 1 day ago By Olivia Odhiambo | 1 day ago By James Omoro | 2 days ago